# Trivy ignore list — vulnerabilities triaged as not-applicable.
# Format: one CVE per line, optional `# reason` after.

# --- github.com/docker/docker (Moby) daemon-side CVEs ---
# Crewship imports docker/docker exclusively as an HTTP API CLIENT
# (api/types, client, pkg/stdcopy stream demultiplexer). None of the
# CVEs below execute in our process — they affect dockerd (the daemon)
# running on the host. Mitigation = upgrade Docker Engine on hosts via
# the OS package manager (apt/yum), not by bumping the Go module.
#
# Go module `github.com/docker/docker` v28.5.2+incompatible is the last
# tagged Go-module release as of 2026-05-23; v29.x exists on GitHub but
# is not yet published to the Go module proxy. Re-evaluate quarterly.
CVE-2026-34040
CVE-2026-41567
CVE-2026-42306
